frameDefinitions: This frame is about the static comparison of an Profiled_item to a Standard_item, often  with respect to some Attribute.
This frame concerns people's knowledge or skill in certain domains.
Compared to its Competitors, a Standard is at the high end of a scale with respect to some Variable.
An Entity (generally food) is exposed to a Heat_source whose Temperature may also be specified.

At a court hearing, a Defendant is informed of the Charges against him or her, (usually) enters a plea, and a decision is made by a Judge as to the amount of bail, if any. '' 'Mortimer and Isabella were hurried off and arraigned before parliament in November.'
This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
frameExamples: The Sun is putting on a show that <t>rivals</t> the most sizzling Hollywood thrillers.
FE Layer-1: He is an <t>experienced</t> programmer.
The taxpayer is supporting a system <t>unmatched</t> in wastefulness .
Bacon was <t>frying</t> in the pan, and a great heap of eggs already lay steaming on a plate.
Mortimer and Isabella were hurried off and <t>arraigned</t> before parliament in November.
listRoleDefinitions: In active sentences, the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> is the grammatically more prominent one of the items that are compared and realized as  the subject. .
In active setnnces, the <fen>Standard_item</fen> is  the grammatically less prominent element, i.e. the object or an oblique.
This Frame Elements marks constituents that indicate in which respect Item-1 and Item-2 are equal to each other.
The <fen>Standard_attribute</fen> is used when the standard is a specific value on  a scale.
The <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen> is a particular value on a scale which is being compared to a <fen>Standard_item</fen> or <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> rivals the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> rivals the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
The person whose expertise is assessed.
<fen>Skill</fen> identifies the <fen>Protagonist</fen>'s talent or ability to do things with one's hand or body.
The area of knowledge (as opposed to a practical skill) in which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> 's experience is assessed.
A  product of behavior that shows the <fen>Protagonist</fen>'s skill or lack of skill.

This frame element can only occur in place of a skill expression. It refers to the prototypical patient in an action involving the Protagonist. For instance, in the following sentence  the children are experts at some (contextually given) action such as rolling the hoops.

<fex name='Protagonist'>Some children</fex> <m>were</m> <fex name='Degree'>quite</fex> <t>expert</t> <fex name='Focal_participant'>with wooden hoops</fex>.
This frame element denotes a role in which the protagonist has developed his expertise.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Protagonist</fen> has the expertise.
The <fen>Standard</fen> is the entity that is located closest to the end of the scale evoked by some <fen>Variable</fen>.
The <fen>Variable</fen> is a property that evokes a scale along which the <fen>Standard</fen> is located closest to one extreme in  comparison to its <fen>Competitors</fen>.
The role <fen>Competitors</fen> denotes the entities that are exceeded by the <fen>Standard</fen> with regard to the <fen>Variable</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> (often a food item)  that absorbs heat.
The <fen>Container</fen> that holds the <fen>Entity</fen> that absorbs the heat.
This role identifies the object that directly supplies heat to the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the heat absorption takes place.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the heat application occurs.
The <fen>Defendant</fen> is charged with a crime by a <fen>Judge</fen>.
The <fen>Judge</fen> is the head of the court where the arraignment occurs.
<fen>Charges</fen> is the crime with which the <fen>Defendant</fen> is charged.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the arraignment occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the arraignment occurs.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
This role marks expressions that denote a scalar property of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> with respect to which the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged.
